Package tage.rml

Interface Matrix3

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Matrix3f
    public interface Matrix3
    This interface defines the operations for a square 3x3 matrix.

    Implementations are meant to use a column-major layout. This is the standard convention followed by mathematical texts and OpenGL/GLSL.

    This interface implies this convention by the overloaded #mult(Vector3) method expecting a vector, where the vector being multiplied is on the right side of the matrix. In other words, a matrix M and a vector v must be multiplied as v' = Mv to produce a new column-vector v' as the output.

    Author:
    Raymond L. Rivera

      • determinant

        float determinant()
        Returns the determinant of this matrix.

        Note that if the determinant is zero, then this matrix is singular and cannot be inverted.

        Returns:
        The determinant of this matrix.

      • inverse

        Matrix3 inverse()
        Returns a new matrix that is the inverse of this matrix, if possible.

        If this matrix is a singular matrix, then it's not possible to calculate its inverse.

        Returns:
        The inverse of this matrix.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - If this is a non-invertible matrix.

      • transpose

        Matrix3 transpose()
        Returns a new matrix that is the transpose of this matrix.

        Transposing a matrix means swapping the columns with the rows.

        Returns:
        The transpose of this matrix.
